<DocsLayout title="Onboarding Migration Guide" description="Migrate from manual server setup to the new onboarding flow.">
  <h1>Onboarding Migration Guide</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-2); font-size: 1.05rem;">
    Replace manual binary copy and hand-authored config with <code>bootstrap</code>, <code>doctor</code>, and profile-based deploy commands.
  </p>

  <h2>Old vs new</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Old: copy binaries manually + write config + write systemd + track host details by hand.</li>
    <li>New: <code>voxeltron bootstrap ...</code> once, then deploy with saved server profiles.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Command mapping</h2>
  <pre><code># old: manual SSH + copy + chmod + service setup
# new:
voxeltron bootstrap &lt;user@host&gt; --profile &lt;name&gt; --yes

# old: manual endpoint notes
# new:
voxeltron server add prod --host 203.0.113.10 --user root
voxeltron server use prod

# old: ad hoc health checks
# new:
voxeltron doctor local
voxeltron doctor remote --server prod

# old: custom deploy wrappers
# new:
voxeltron deploy nginx --name hello --server prod --wait --json</code></pre>

  <h2>Compatibility notes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Digest image refs (<code>image@sha256:...</code>) are not supported yet in deploy flow.</li>
    <li>Tagged image deploys are supported and no longer append duplicate tags.</li>
  </ul>

